# ── Browser push notifications (VAPID / W3C Web Push) ─────────────────────────
# Standard browser push — works in Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari 16.4+.
# No third-party relay needed. The server signs push messages with the key pair
# and sends them directly to the browser's push service.
#
# VAPID_SUBJECT — contact URI shown to push services; use mailto: or https:
# VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY  — URL-safe base64 public key (from web-push or npx web-push generate-vapid-keys)
# VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY — URL-safe base64 private key (keep secret)
#
# To generate a new key pair:
#   npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
#
# The public key is served at GET /api/push/vapid-public-key and used by the
# frontend to subscribe via PushManager.subscribe({ applicationServerKey }).
VAPID_SUBJECT=mailto:noreply@flightsuite.app
VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=

# ── Push webhook relay (optional fallback) ─────────────────────────────────────
# If VAPID keys are set, VAPID is used preferentially for users who have subscribed.
# Set PUSH_WEBHOOK_URL as a fallback for users without a browser subscription
# (e.g. ntfy.sh, a self-hosted relay, or a mobile push gateway).
# When neither VAPID nor webhook is configured, alerts go to dead-letter only.
